    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2011-06-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2011-07-22T19:09:35Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Steel Industry Support Act of 2011 - Amends Internal Revenue Code, with respect to the tax credit for the production of electricity from renewable resources, to: (1) extend through FY2018 the credit period for the production of steel industry fuel; (2) extend through June 30, 2012, the placed-in-service date requirement for refined coal production facilities; (3) revise the definition of &quot;steel industry fuel&quot; to allow mixtures of petroleum coke or other coke feedstock in such fuel; and (4) set forth ownership requirements for coal production facilities for purposes of such tax credit.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
